## AD Object Types

| Object Type | Description | Attacker Interest |
|-------------|-------------|-------------------|
| User accounts | Human or service accounts | Credential targets, delegation abuse |
| Computer accounts | Domain-joined machines | Lateral movement targets |
| Groups | Collections of users/computers | High-privilege groups are primary targets |
| Service accounts | Non-human accounts running services | Kerberoasting targets (have SPNs) |
| GPOs | Policy objects linked to OUs | Misconfigured write access = domain compromise |

### High-Value Groups

These groups represent the most critical targets during AD enumeration:

| Group | Privilege Level |
|-------|----------------|
| Domain Admins | Full control over the domain |
| Enterprise Admins | Full control over the entire forest |
| Schema Admins | Can modify the AD schema |
| Backup Operators | Can read NTDS.dit — effective domain compromise |
| Server Operators | Can run commands on DCs |
| Account Operators | Can create/modify most user accounts |

