## Group Policy Objects (GPOs)

GPOs allow administrators to enforce settings across all machines and users in an OU — password policies, software installation, login scripts, registry settings, firewall rules.

**Attacker relevance:** If you gain write access to a GPO linked to an OU containing privileged users or computers, you can push arbitrary commands to every machine in that OU as SYSTEM. This is an immediate domain compromise vector.

```bash
# Enumerate GPOs during AD enumeration
Get-GPO -All                           # PowerShell (on domain machine)
bloodhound-python -c GPOs             # BloodHound collection
```

