## Enumeration Commands Reference

Commands used throughout Phase 5 when working inside an AD environment:

```powershell
# Domain information
Get-ADDomain
[System.DirectoryServices.ActiveDirectory.Domain]::GetCurrentDomain()

# User enumeration
Get-ADUser -Filter * -Properties *
net user /domain

# Group enumeration  
Get-ADGroup -Filter * | Select Name
net group /domain
net group "Domain Admins" /domain

# Computer enumeration
Get-ADComputer -Filter * | Select Name
net view /domain

# SPN enumeration (Kerberoasting targets)
Get-ADUser -Filter {ServicePrincipalName -ne "$null"} -Properties ServicePrincipalName

# Check for AS-REP Roasting candidates
Get-ADUser -Filter {DoesNotRequirePreAuth -eq $true} -Properties DoesNotRequirePreAuth
```

From Linux (unauthenticated or with credentials):

```bash
# Enumerate with enum4linux
enum4linux -a <dc-ip>

# LDAP enumeration
ldapsearch -x -H ldap://<dc-ip> -b "dc=corp,dc=local"

# BloodHound collection (most comprehensive)
bloodhound-python -u <user> -p <password> -d <domain> -dc <dc-ip> -c All
```

